SingTel service extended to Saudi Arabia . Singapore Telecom said on Thursday its PhoneHome Card service will be extended to Saudi Arabia from December 1 this year . A company statement said callers using the facility no longer have to speak to an operator , pay hotel surcharges , or queue for a public telephone . Callers will have the option of charging to international calling cards or calling collect . Other Singapore Telecom services such as SingaporeDirect , HomeEasy Dial , and Enhanced Call Home have been available in Saudi Arabia since September this year . - - Singapore newsroom 65 - 8703080 
